    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Event4AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3,T4>, Event4Delegate<T1,T2,T3,T4>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Action4AsyncSupport, Action4ToAsyncAction4, Event4AsyncAdapter, Event4Caller, Event4Distributor
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Action4<T1,T2,T3,T4>
    An Action4 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Author:
    tilmann
